HEADWORD: Brucite
<hw>Bru"cite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after Dr. A.
<etsep>Bruce</etsep> of New York.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A white, pearly mineral, occurring thin and foliated, like talc,
and also fibrous; a native magnesium hydrate.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The mineral chondrodite.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bruckeled</ent>⟦br⟧
